content.thinking:
I can see the issue clearly:

```json
"channels": {
    "feishu": {
      "enabled": true,
      "defaultAccount": "kiit",
      "accounts": {
        "kiit": {
          "appId": "cli_a93650c6fc785bce",
          "appSecret": "***",
          "name": "kiit",
          "enabled": true,
          "streaming": false    // <-- account-level streaming is FALSE
        },
        "tts": { ... }
      },
      "streaming": true,       // <-- channel-level streaming is TRUE
      ...
    }
}
```

The channel-level `streaming: true` is overridden by the account-level `streaming: false` on `kiit`. 

Since the account-level setting is more specific, streaming is disabled for this account. Feishu supports streaming through its `stream_messages` API, so I need to flip the account-level `kiit` streaming flag to `true`.

